<item>
            <title>[LU-17987] always trust OST last_id in normal precreate</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17987</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In normal precreate (not the first one which will try deleting orphans) the last_id on OST is always trustable, because it&apos;s maintained in memory, and rarely OSP may try to precreate with a stale last_id (even more than OST_MAX_PRECREATE), it should be OSP that messes up the last created FID, always reply OSP with current last_id, so that OST won&apos;t become unusable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
